        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1030" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1030">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/7–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 1030<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WJG2" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Political Adviser to the Representative on
                        the European Advisory Commission</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MPE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mosely</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d1030fn1">For the full text of this message, see
                            <ref target="#d1035">document No. 1035</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-18">18 July
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tripartite Conference Babelsberg for <persName corresp="#p_MPE1">Mosely</persName> from <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName> serial
                    number 4307.</p>
                <p>… No word to date received at Soviet Embassy here from Moscow permitting
                    clearance and signature of … agreement amending agreement on zones Germany.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
